.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-8-4::.
City: paris, marseilles, rome, venice
The people use 4 different means of transport: boat, car, quad-bike, subway
There 4 different types of food: garlic, spinach, cauliflower, corn
 1. the person traveling to marseilles is on the left of the person driving the subway##1
 2. the person eating spinach is not to the left of the person driving the car##8
 3. the person driving the subway is somewhere to the right of the person traveling to paris##5
 4. the person traveling to paris is on the far left##1
 5. the person traveling to marseilles is not to the right of the person eating spinach##8
 6. the person eating cauliflower is not to the right of the person traveling to venice##8
 7. the person driving the quad-bike is somewhere to the left of the person traveling to venice##5
 8. the person eating corn is somewhere to the right of the person eating spinach##5
 9. the person eating garlic is on the left of the person eating cauliflower##1
10. the person traveling to venice is the person eating cauliflower##1
11. the person driving the boat is somewhere to the right of the person driving the car##5

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1    |    2     |     3     |    4    |
| City   | paris   | venice | marseilles    | rome |
| Transport   | quad-bike    | car     | boat   | subway     |
| Food   | garlic | cauliflower   | spinach | corn    |

